but we’re not liable for it ourselves; the user who posted is. Similarly, if you download something from Duvdu that turns out to have a virus (unlikely if it passed our virus scans, but just hypothetically) or infringing material, we didn’t put it there – a User did. Our liability for that is disclaimed.</p><p><strong>No Liability for Interruption or Errors:</strong> If the Platform is unavailable or errors occur (like messages not going through, a proposal not getting saved, etc.), Duvdu isn’t liable for losses resulting from that. We will, of course, try to fix issues, but you can’t claim damages because you missed a project due to downtime or similar.</p><p><strong>Maximum Extent of Law:</strong> We include language that basically says, <i>even if some of these exclusions or limitations don’t apply in a certain jurisdiction, our liability will be limited to the maximum extent the law allows</i>. We want our liability to be as limited as possible. If one part of this section is invalid under the law, the rest still applies.</p><p><strong>Indemnity and Liability:</strong> A note that often in these agreements, if someone else sues Duvdu for something you did, you indemnify us (that’s in the next section). So that also plays into liability – we push certain liabilities back onto the user if they were the cause.</p><p><strong>Example Scenario:</strong> To illustrate, suppose a bug in Duvdu’s code caused a message from a Client to not reach a Freelancer, and the Freelancer misses out on a job that would pay EGP EGP 20,000. The Freelancer cannot claim that lost opportunity cost from Duvdu. At most, they might point out the bug and maybe we’d fix it and might give a token courtesy credit or something (that’s not obligatory, just a goodwill measure). But under these Terms, we wouldn’t owe the EGP 20,000 revenue they missed. We encourage everyone to mitigate their own risk (keep backups of work, use good security practices, not solely rely on one platform for communication, etc.).</p><p><strong>Acknowledgment:</strong> By using Duvdu, you acknowledge that you understand the risk allocation in these Terms. The fees we charge would likely be higher if we had to assume a lot of risk. This limitation of liability is a core part of our agreement and is reflected in the pricing of our services (which for Users is basically the subscription fee). Without these limitations, we could not feasibly provide the Platform services at the current cost structure.</p><p><strong>Indemnification</strong></p><p>Indemnification is a way for one party to step up and cover costs/losses of another party if certain things happen. In this context, <strong>you agree to indemnify Duvdu</strong> (and related parties) if your actions cause us to be sued or incur damages, as detailed below.</p><p><strong>Your Agreement to Indemnify:</strong> You (the User) agree to <strong>defend, indemnify, and hold harmless</strong> Duvdu, its parent company, subsidiaries, affiliates, and their respective officers, directors, employees, and agents (the “Indemnified Parties”) from and against any and all <strong>claims, liabilities, losses, damages, judgments, awards, costs, and expenses (including reasonable legal fees)</strong> that arise out of or relate to:</p><ul><li><strong>Your breach of these Terms:</strong> If you violate any provision of this Agreement, and that causes harm or a legal claim against Duvdu. For example, if you breach the confidentiality clause and post a client’s secret info publicly, and then the client sues Duvdu for not protecting that info, you would indemnify Duvdu for any loss.</li><li><strong>Your use of the Platform:</strong> This is broad – it covers any misuse or even proper use that has unintended consequences. If you do something on the Platform that results in a claim. For instance, you upload content you don’t have rights to and the actual owner of that content sues Duvdu for infringement, you must indemnify us (cover our costs/damages). Or if as a freelancer you provide defective work that somehow injures someone and they bring a claim against us as the platform, you indemnify us.</li><li><strong>Your dispute with another user:</strong> If you get into a legal dispute with another user and somehow drag Duvdu into it (like you sue the other user and also sue Duvdu or they sue Duvdu claiming we’re responsible), you agree to indemnify us for any liability or costs.</li><li><strong>Your violation of any law or rights:</strong> If you, for example, violate intellectual property laws (post someone’s copyrighted material, etc.) or defame someone via the platform, or violate privacy laws, and Duvdu is sued or fined because of that, you will cover our costs. Also if you violate any third-party rights (like someone’s patent or trademark or a person’s privacy rights) via content you upload or actions you take on Duvdu.</li><li><strong>Any contract or promised made to another user:</strong> We are not a party to user-user contracts, but if somehow a user sues us claiming we should be responsible for your contractual breach, you indemnify us. E.g., a client sues Duvdu saying “you should have ensured the freelancer delivered”; even though we disclaim that, if we incur legal costs, we’d turn to you for indemnification.</li></ul><p><strong>Defense:</strong> “Defend” means you also agree to handle the defense in such claims. Usually, this means if Duvdu is named in a lawsuit due to your actions, Duvdu can require that you step in and manage (and pay for) the legal defense (hiring lawyers, going to court, etc.), or at least reimburse those costs. We may choose to handle it ourselves but at your expense if we want to maintain control – often the contract will state we can elect to do our own defense.</p><p><strong>Cooperation:</strong> If Duvdu is facing a claim that triggers your indemnity, we will likely notify you and expect your cooperation. You might have to provide us with information or testify or things like that as part of the defense.</p><p><strong>Settlements:</strong> Typically, we’ll include that you cannot settle any claim on behalf of Duvdu or that implicates Duvdu without our written consent (because a settlement could impose obligations or admissions on us). Conversely, if we want to settle something that you’re indemnifying us for, we might seek your approval (especially if it might put obligations on you). But usually, since indemnity is your responsibility, we might allow you to settle as long as it doesn’t harm us.</p><p><strong>Legal Fees:</strong> Note that indemnification includes covering our attorneys’ fees and court costs. Legal processes can be expensive, and if due to your actions we have to spend on lawyers, you agree to pay those bills.</p><p><strong>Example scenario:</strong> A Freelancer posts a portfolio piece on Duvdu that actually belongs to another designer, claiming it as their own. The other designer finds out and sends Duvdu a legal notice or files a lawsuit for copyright infringement, naming Duvdu (for hosting it) and the Freelancer. In that case, the Freelancer must indemnify Duvdu – meaning they would need to pay for Duvdu’s legal defense and any settlement or judgment against Duvdu, because it was the Freelancer’s wrongful action that caused it. Or say a Client had the Freelancer do some illegal task (like scraping data unlawfully) and some party sues Duvdu as well for facilitating it – the Client would indemnify us.</p><p><strong>Additional Protection:</strong> This indemnity extends to all our affiliated entities and personnel. So if a claim is made against our CEO or an employee because of something a user did, the user indemnifies them as well.</p><p><strong>Notification:</strong> Usually, we will promptly notify you if we receive a claim that we believe you should indemnify us for. We’ll give you information and perhaps let you handle it or join in handling it.</p><p>This section is basically saying: <strong>be responsible for your